schemacrawler.crawl

Class MetadataResultSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • schemacrawler.crawl.MetadataResultSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable

    public final class MetadataResultSet
extends Object
implements AutoCloseable
    A wrapper around a JDBC resultset obtained from a database metadata call. This allows type-safe methods to obtain boolean, integer and string data, while abstracting away the quirks of the JDBC metadata API.
    Author:
    Sualeh Fatehi

      • next

        public boolean next()
             throws SQLException
        Moves the cursor down one row from its current position. A ResultSet cursor is initially positioned before the first row; the first call to the method next makes the first row the current row; the second call makes the second row the current row, and so on.
        Returns:
        true if the new current row is valid; false if there are no more rows
        Throws:
        SQLException - On a database access error
